.TH AUTOSHELF 1 "2026-04-22" "autoshelf 1.0.26" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
autoshelf \- offline-first folder organizer with preview, audit, and recovery workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B autoshelf
[global-options] command [command-options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
autoshelf scans a root, drafts a reversible organization plan, lets the operator preview the result, applies moves plus shortcuts, and emits manifest-driven audit artifacts for verify and undo.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-level LOG_LEVEL\fR
No additional details.
.TP
\fB\-\-config CONFIG\fR
No additional details.
.TP
\fB\-\-progress PROGRESS\fR
No additional details.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS apply
Apply a planned folder layout
.br
Usage: autoshelf apply [\-h] [\-\-resume RESUME] [\-\-dry\-run] [\-\-policy POLICY]
                       [\-\-yes]
                       root
.RS
.TP
\fBroot ROOT\fR
No additional details.
.TP
\fB\-\-resume RESUME\fR
No additional details.
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
No additional details.
.TP
\fB\-\-policy POLICY\fR
No additional details.
.TP
\fB\-\-yes\fR
No additional details.
.RE
.SS config
